Debut Album

The beginning of my exploration into the goodness of God. This album documents my first steps as a believer, walking in 'The Way'. Music from and for the soul. Spirit filled. The tracks range from groove to ambient. One thing each track shares in common, is that they are all love songs. Inspiration has come through the process of revealing that God has lead me through. Musical styles and artists have also had an impact, jazz, r&b, hip-hop, Ledisi, Lisa McClendon, Rachelle Ferrell. However above all I have been inspired by Love & Light. May this album be as much of a blessing to all who hears as it has been to me. Peace

title: Dont Fall In Love (feat. Qewl Miles)
LOVE ME OR LET ME GO
extra:
Think Linda Ronstadt meets Patsy Cline & Bonnie Raitt.

Thats what you get from the debut EP of blues rock artist Julia Alyce. A collection of music that Julia co-wrote in collaboration with music producer Maia Sharp who's written popular songs for Bonnie Raitt, & Trisha Yearwood among others.

An album that any fan of the aforementioned artists should add to their collection.

Julias EP features the steel guitar work of music legend Greg Leisz, whos played on many of Joni Mitchells albums. Other well-known musicians featured include: Maia Sharp (Producer, Piano, & multiple instruments), Linda Taylor (Guitar), David J. Carpenter (Bass), and Brian Macleod (Drums).

Julias in it for the love of the entire music process. Not for any individual moments but for the entire ride. The whole production has a cosmic vibe to it as well.

All three songs on the EP reflect different aspects of love.

When I made this song, I didn't want to create an image of lovey dubby type song. Instead I thought of the girl I wrote it for and decyphered her personality. She's real gangsta and down for me so The chorus was designed by "Poor Da Rico" to give it that melody and rhythm that I want people to dance to. The chorus states "Even if I catch a case, she posts my bail and keep me sane" which states she knows the life style of people catching cases and going to jail. It also tells that she's down for me no matter what type of life style I live. Then the lyrics I wrote in the song were deep and the metaphors are easy to follow so it's still MUSIC and not just a bunch of words I through together. I write music no rap.

title: Lay-Leezy Ft Young Moe - Change My Faith (Produced By Rhome 616)
confidential land, untouchable sand
extra:
tutto fatto con una chitarra e una loop station.

La base un semplice 4/4, con l'accento (la cassa) sul primo quarto.
Per il giro (riff) principale dura 10/4 (6+4), quindi l'inizio dei riff pari sono spostati di due quarti rispetto alla cassa.

Il pezzo che ho registrato strutturato come segue:

A) click x8
B) riff x4
C) bass x4
D) chords x4
E) riff x4
F) dist x4
G) light x4
H) solo x8

in sostanza ogni quattro giri (10/4) viene aggiunto uno strato.

Un'idea potrebbe essere, posto che una strofa ci stia sulla durata di 4 giri, cantare su B,C,E,G.

Naturalmente tutto questo schema si pu stravolgere come fa pi comodo.
